:R-HSA-418594  a            obo:GO_0008150 , owl:NamedIndividual ;
        rdfs:comment        "The classical signalling mechanism for G alpha (i) is inhibition of the cAMP dependent pathway through inhibition of adenylate cyclase (Dessauer C W et al. 2002). Decreased production of cAMP from ATP results in decreased activity of cAMP-dependent protein kinases. Other functions of G alpha (i) includes activation of the protein tyrosine kinase c-Src (Ma Y C et al. 2000). Regulator of G-protein Signalling (RGS) proteins can regulate the activity of G alpha (i) (Soundararajan et al. 2008)." ;
        rdfs:label          "G alpha (i) signalling events" ;
        dc:contributor      "Authored: Jupe, S, 2009-05-01 15:23:43" , "GOC:reactome_curators" , "Reviewed: Akkerman, JW, 2009-06-03" , "Edited: Jupe, S, 2009-05-01 15:23:43" ;
        dc:date             "2026-06-29" ;
        pav:providedBy      "https://reactome.org" ;
        oboInOwl:hasDbXref  "R-HSA-418594" ;
        skos:narrower       <http://model.geneontology.org/R-HSA-388396/R-HSA-388396> ;
        skos:note           "org.biopax.paxtools.model.level3.Pathway" .

